mibsystemProfileTable.name: mibsystemProfileTable
mibsystemProfileTable.description: A list of mibsystemProfile profile entries.

mibsystemProfileEntry.name: mibsystemProfileEntry
mibsystemProfileEntry.description: A mibsystemProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibsystemProfile profile.

systemProfile_Name.name: systemProfile_Name
systemProfile_Name.description: The name of the system given by the user, a standard null terminated ASCII string.

systemProfile_Contact.name: systemProfile_Contact
systemProfile_Contact.description: The name of the contact for this device. SNMP readable.

systemProfile_Location.name: systemProfile_Location
systemProfile_Location.description: The location of this device. SNMP readable.

systemProfile_TermRate.name: systemProfile_TermRate
systemProfile_TermRate.description: The bit rate of the management terminal port, as given above.

systemProfile_Console.name: systemProfile_Console
systemProfile_Console.description: A MenuType specifying the type of interface to use on the console port.

systemProfile_ConsoleSecurity.name: systemProfile_ConsoleSecurity
systemProfile_ConsoleSecurity.description: Serial console security for the control port.

systemProfile_SystemRmtMgmt.name: systemProfile_SystemRmtMgmt
systemProfile_SystemRmtMgmt.description: Set true if this system allows remote management.

systemProfile_SubAddressMode.name: systemProfile_SubAddressMode
systemProfile_SubAddressMode.description: Selects system wide sub-address support. See mibglob.mdf for details.

systemProfile_SerialSubaddress.name: systemProfile_SerialSubaddress
systemProfile_SerialSubaddress.description: sub-address assigned to serial port connections.

systemProfile_LanSubaddress.name: systemProfile_LanSubaddress
systemProfile_LanSubaddress.description: sub-address assigned to sync lan connections.

systemProfile_DmSubaddress.name: systemProfile_DmSubaddress
systemProfile_DmSubaddress.description: sub-address assigned to digital modem connections.

systemProfile_V110Subaddress.name: systemProfile_V110Subaddress
systemProfile_V110Subaddress.description: sub-address assigned to V.110 rate adaption connections

systemProfile_UseTrunkGroups.name: systemProfile_UseTrunkGroups
systemProfile_UseTrunkGroups.description: Enables TrunkGroups for all network lines.

systemProfile_NumDigitsTrunkGroups.name: systemProfile_NumDigitsTrunkGroups
systemProfile_NumDigitsTrunkGroups.description: Specify number of digits TrunkGroups support.

systemProfile_AutoLogout.name: systemProfile_AutoLogout
systemProfile_AutoLogout.description: When TRUE select the default security profile on loss of CD/DTR from the main console port.

systemProfile_IdleLogout.name: systemProfile_IdleLogout
systemProfile_IdleLogout.description: When non-zero select the default security profile after this value of minutes with no keyboard activity.

systemProfile_oDS0MinRst.name: systemProfile_oDS0MinRst
systemProfile_oDS0MinRst.description: Has three choices: Off, 24Hr or Monthly. When enabled, the following maxSystemDS0Mins is the high water mark at which all switched connections originating on the system will be taken down.

systemProfile_MaxSystemDS0Mins.name: systemProfile_MaxSystemDS0Mins
systemProfile_MaxSystemDS0Mins.description: Sets the high water billing mark at which all originating switched connections are brought down.

systemProfile_MaxDialoutTime.name: systemProfile_MaxDialoutTime
systemProfile_MaxDialoutTime.description: The max time in Sec, system will wait for Call Setup Complete

systemProfile_ParallelDialing.name: systemProfile_ParallelDialing
systemProfile_ParallelDialing.description: The number of simultaneous DS0 channel outdials the switch allows.

systemProfile_SingleFileIncoming.name: systemProfile_SingleFileIncoming
systemProfile_SingleFileIncoming.description: Should the calls be treated as a single-file list, or in parallel. PictureTel wants parallel others want single-file.

systemProfile_DelayDualPortDialing.name: systemProfile_DelayDualPortDialing
systemProfile_DelayDualPortDialing.description: TRUE if we should delay between dual port calls, FALSE if they should be placed at the same time.

systemProfile_EditNumber.name: systemProfile_EditNumber
systemProfile_EditNumber.description: The menu number of the default edit screen.

systemProfile_AnalogEncoding.name: systemProfile_AnalogEncoding
systemProfile_AnalogEncoding.description: Sets the encoding standard for digitized analog data to either u-Law or A-Law. Universally sets all codecs on the unit to the value selected. Defaults to u-Law for T1, A-Law for E1 interfaces.

systemProfile_TOnline.name: systemProfile_TOnline
systemProfile_TOnline.description: TRUE if we should route calls to T-Online, FALSE if not.

systemProfile_TOnlineMostAvailChan.name: systemProfile_TOnlineMostAvailChan
systemProfile_TOnlineMostAvailChan.description: TRUE if T-Online calls are to be routed to NT line with the most available B-channels FALSE if it is based on circular basis.

systemProfile_T302Timer.name: systemProfile_T302Timer
systemProfile_T302Timer.description: Number of milliseconds to wait for additional called number information elements for an incoming T-Online call. Defaults to 1500.

systemProfile_CallRoutingSortMethod.name: systemProfile_CallRoutingSortMethod
systemProfile_CallRoutingSortMethod.description: How to sort the Call Routing table for analog calls.

systemProfile_DigitalCallRoutingSortMeth.name: systemProfile_DigitalCallRoutingSortMethod
systemProfile_DigitalCallRoutingSortMeth.description: How to sort the Call Routing table for digital calls.

systemProfile_ExactMatchCallRouting.name: systemProfile_ExactMatchCallRouting
systemProfile_ExactMatchCallRouting.description: If yes, the system will search for an exact match of call-route profile parameters when selecting devices. Wildcard matches will be accepted only after all 4 quadrants have been searched. (APX only)

systemProfile_ShelfControllerType.name: systemProfile_ShelfControllerType
systemProfile_ShelfControllerType.description: Used to define the role of this controller in a single-shelf or multi-shelf system. Note: This variable is not applicable to the APX 8000.

systemProfile_MasterShelfController.name: systemProfile_MasterShelfController
systemProfile_MasterShelfController.description: Master shelf controller number. This attribute exists only when the shelf-controller-type is SLAVE. Note: This variable is not applicable to the APX 8000.

systemProfile_NewNasPortIdFormat.name: systemProfile_NewNasPortIdFormat
systemProfile_NewNasPortIdFormat.description: Field is deprecated; use the 'nas-port-format' field to specify the NAS port format. Will be used only if 'nas-port-format' is set to 'not-applicable'. TRUE if new NAS port ID format is used, FALSE if old NAS Port ID is used. On the TNT product family the new NAS port ID format is used by default. The old format cannot be used for multi-shelf systems or if any line cards are in a slot greater than the twelfth position.

systemProfile_NasPortFormat.name: systemProfile_NasPortFormat
systemProfile_NasPortFormat.description: Specifies NAS-Port-Format used to calculate the NAS-Port-ID. When set to 'not-applicable', indicates that the NAS Port Format is determined by the settings in the 'new-nas-port-id-format' field. Defaults to 'not-applicable'.

systemProfile_ModemPriTypeOfNumber.name: systemProfile_ModemPriTypeOfNumber
systemProfile_ModemPriTypeOfNumber.description: PRI Called Party element's Type-Of-Number value for outgoing modem calls.

systemProfile_ModemPriNumberingPlanId.name: systemProfile_ModemPriNumberingPlanId
systemProfile_ModemPriNumberingPlanId.description: PRI Called Party element's Numbering-Plan-ID value for outgoing modem calls.

systemProfile_WanInterface.name: systemProfile_WanInterface
systemProfile_WanInterface.description: Sets the type of WAN interface supported: T1-CSU or Serial WAN.

systemProfile_PermConnUpdMode.name: systemProfile_PermConnUpdMode
systemProfile_PermConnUpdMode.description: Enables nonintrusive remote update of permanent connections' configurations. 'Changed' means that only changed connections will be torn down and reestablished, 'All' means all existing permanent connections will be turn down and then reestablished only if they are fetched from the RADIUS server again

systemProfile_UserstatFormat.name: systemProfile_UserstatFormat
systemProfile_UserstatFormat.description: Defines the output format of the session listing command 'userstat' and the remote user information protocol 'finger'. The following special characters will be converted to their values for each listed session. The width of each field is indicated in []. %i [10] SessionID, Unique ID assigned to the session. %l [10] Line/Chan, Physical address (shelf.slot.line/chan). %s [11] Slot:Item, shelf:slot:item/logical-item of the host port. %r [11] Tx/Rx Rate, Transmit and receive rates. %d [ 3] Svc, A three-letter code showing the type of service. %a [15] Address, IP address. %u [14] Username, Connection profile name. %c [10] ConnTime, Ammount of time connected in hours:minutes:seconds. %t [10] IdleTime, Ammount of time idle in hours:minutes:seconds. %n [24] Dialed#, Number dialed if known. %f [24] Calling#, Number calling from if known. For example set userstat-format = '%i %l %s %r %d %a %u %c %t %n' would set the format to the factory default value.

systemProfile_ControlBusType.name: systemProfile_ControlBusType
systemProfile_ControlBusType.description: How to send control bus messages. This attribute exists only when the shelf-controller-type is not SLAVE.

systemProfile_BootSrVersion.name: systemProfile_BootSrVersion
systemProfile_BootSrVersion.description: Place for tntsrb, the shelf controller boot loader, to provide its version. Boot loader updates the field with its version on every system reset

systemProfile_SysModemProfile_oATAnswerS.name: systemProfile_SysModemProfile_oATAnswerString
systemProfile_SysModemProfile_oATAnswerS.description: Allows the user to enter any additional AT commands in the modem answer string.

systemProfile_CallByCall.name: systemProfile_CallByCall
systemProfile_CallByCall.description: PRI Called Party element's Network Specific Facility for Call-by-Call.

systemProfile_Country.name: systemProfile_Country
systemProfile_Country.description: Country in which the system is located.

systemProfile_SupportDbcs.name: systemProfile_SupportDbcs
systemProfile_SupportDbcs.description: TRUE if we should support DBCS character set, FALSE if not.

systemProfile_IncCallDistrib.name: systemProfile_IncCallDistrib
systemProfile_IncCallDistrib.description: Route incoming calls to first available valid port or the least used among a set of ports.

systemProfile_IgnoreLineup.name: systemProfile_IgnoreLineup
systemProfile_IgnoreLineup.description: If ignore-lineup in line config profile is set to SYSTEM DEFINED, then this will take precedence.

systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile1.name: systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile1
systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile1.description: File name of the first JAM file's component

systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile2.name: systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile2
systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile2.description: File name of the second JAM file's component

systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile3.name: systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile3
systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile3.description: File name of the third JAM file's component

systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile4.name: systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile4
systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile4.description: File name of the fourth JAM file's component

systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile5.name: systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile5
systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile5.description: File name of the fifth JAM file's component

systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile6.name: systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile6
systemProfile_JamFileComponents_JamFile6.description: File name of the sixth JAM file's component
